        'Let me close a loop that\'s been running since Module 2.',
        'We talk about knowledge as if it\'s one thing. You either know something or you don\'t. The entire educational system is built on this model — information in, stored, retrievable on demand. And within its own domain, that model is fine. But it is catastrophically incomplete as a description of what skill is and how it develops.',
        'There are actually two completely different types of knowing, and confusing them is responsible for a significant portion of the stagnation in human skill development.',
